<P>A DRAMA.</P>
<P>IN ONE PART.</P>
<Q><L>Ble&s;s'd too is he who&s;e evening ramble &s;tray<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"></L>
<L>Where droop the &s;ons of indigence and care;</L>
<L>His little gift their gladden'd eyes <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">,</L>
<L>And <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> at &s;mall expence their <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">onde&s;t pray'<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"></L>
<BIBL><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">HENSTONE.</BIBL></Q>
